  <prompt>
    Build two net-new wizard widgets that open the Analysis Builder pre-configured for two
    specific intents per FR-19:
    (a) `email-compose` â€” Analysis Builder configured for the compose-email flow (triggered
        from the GetStartedCards "Send Email" card).
    (b) `meeting-schedule` â€” Analysis Builder configured for the schedule-meeting flow
        (triggered from the GetStartedCards "Schedule Meeting" card).
    Both register in `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry`. First step: search the repo for the existing
    Analysis Builder invocation API to determine the correct contract for passing an intent.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React 19 + Fluent v9 frontend developer experienced with AI Analysis Builder workflows,
    widget wrappers, and widget-registry registration patterns. Comfortable searching the
    codebase to discover existing component contracts before authoring new wrappers.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Two new files exist under `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/`:
    `EmailComposeWidget.tsx` (or canonical name) and `MeetingScheduleWidget.tsx` (or canonical
    name). Each renders the Analysis Builder component pre-configured with the appropriate
    intent (`'email-compose'` or `'meeting-schedule'`). Both are registered in
    `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry` under widget types `email-compose` and `meeting-schedule`
    respectively (these MUST match task 042's dispatched strings). When a `widget_load`
    event for either type fires on the `workspace` channel, the corresponding widget opens
    Analysis Builder in the correct mode.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-19 routes Send Email and Schedule Meeting GetStartedCards card clicks to the
      Analysis Builder â€” Spaarke's existing AI-driven multi-step composition surface. Rather
      than building new bespoke wizards, the cards leverage Analysis Builder pre-configured
      with the appropriate intent. The exact invocation contract (prop name, value space) is
      to be discovered from existing usage in the codebase â€” Analysis Builder is already
      shipping somewhere in src/, and the search-first approach honors OC-04 reuse.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/EmailComposeWidget.tsx</file>
