  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Analysis Builder is consumed from its existing location â€” do NOT copy-paste its internals. Use the canonical invocation API discovered in step 1.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">No hex literals, no `rgba(...)` literals, no Fluent v8. Wrapper styling (minimal) uses `tokens.*`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 only. No React 16 fallbacks.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-025">Any icons used (e.g., for tab title or wrapper chrome) come from `@fluentui/react-icons` Fluent v9.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No `accessToken` props or state in the wrappers. Analysis Builder uses `authenticatedFetch` internally per ADR-028 â€” verify by grep before relying on it. If a token snapshot is present in Analysis Builder, flag as a finding (separate fix outside this task).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-19 widget_type strings MUST match exactly: `email-compose` and `meeting-schedule`. These are the strings dispatched by task 042's onCardClick handler.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">If Analysis Builder lives in a solution package, import via the package boundary (don't reach into private internals). If it does not expose an intent-prefill API today, document the gap in `notes/` and choose between (a) adding the API as part of this task or (b) opening a follow-up â€” but do NOT build a fake Analysis Builder copy.</constraint>
  </constraints>

