  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Discover Analysis Builder invocation API">
      Grep the repo for `AnalysisBuilder`, `analysis-builder`, `analysisBuilder`. Locate the
      component/entry point (likely in `src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/` or similar).
      Read its prop signature to determine how an "intent" is passed (prop name might be
      `intent`, `mode`, `prefilledAction`, or similar). Document the contract in the wrapper
      file header comment.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="If no intent-prefill API exists, decide path">
      If Analysis Builder does not accept an intent today, choose:
      <steps>
        <step>Option A: Add an `intent?: string` prop to Analysis Builder + ship in this task (small, well-scoped).</step>
        <step>Option B: Open a follow-up + ship the widgets as placeholders that route to Analysis Builder without prefill (degraded behavior).</step>
      </steps>
      Prefer Option A if the change is small. Document the choice in `notes/` and surface to the user
      if scope expands significantly.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Create EmailComposeWidget.tsx (or canonical name)">
      Scaffold a thin wrapper that renders Analysis Builder with `intent='email-compose'`.
      Component should be self-contained â€” it manages no state beyond rendering Analysis
      Builder in the correct mode and handling widget-tab lifecycle (open/close).
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Create MeetingScheduleWidget.tsx (or canonical name)">
      Analogous to step 3, with `intent='meeting-schedule'`.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Register both in WorkspaceWidgetRegistry">
      Add registrations using the existing pattern (lazy-import factory). Widget types
      `email-compose` and `meeting-schedule` MUST match task 042's dispatched strings exactly.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Smoke-test via widget_load event">
      Build the Spaarke.AI.Widgets package and consuming solution. Click "Send Email" card in
      GetStartedCards â€” confirm Analysis Builder opens in compose-email mode. Click "Schedule
      Meeting" â€” confirm Analysis Builder opens in schedule-meeting mode.
    </step>
  </steps>

